{
  "stem": "22047.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was-- in one case, there was a-- a building that-- that they were actually housed in and guarded by a few German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had not been treated that badly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Men and women-- the women were segregated from the men.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there were men and women and-- and young people, children, some children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were several children, corpses of children in-- in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think the-- the camp seemed to be split in-- in two, with-- with the women on this side and the men on this side.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then they had, just inside this gate that I showed you, were some buildings that I guess the more elite prisoners were kept, like this Belgian officer and some others-- some other officers.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a Frenchman and a-- a Polish officer were in-- housed in this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were treated a little less severe than the others.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went-- we actually went on a kind of a right angle [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] trail, Wurzburg.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we turned south and went through Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we went kind of-- kind of like a-- a right turn and went to Munich and on south of Munich, all the way into Austria.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We ended the war actually in southern Austria.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Our job in Austria was to go into the Alps and ferret out those Germans that had fled south.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Our intelligence said that they are holed up in the Alps, in various places in the Alps, and go find them, most of all, to tell them the war's over.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Don't fight it anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You can go home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we found a few.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, that was the only one.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
